   MAGAZINES-SPINOFFS (Undated) _ In the last two years, publishers
have come to see the spinoff as the future of magazines. Spinoffs
are new magazines that take the title of the original publication
and, by adding a subtitle like ``For Women,'' ``Finance'' or
``Gardener,'' try to attract new readers and provide a new
marketplace for advertisers. By Alex Kuczynski.
