<P>
   MILOSEVIC-PROFILE-TWOTAKES (Undated) _ Yugoslav President
Slobodan Milosevic creates disorder and manages to convince people
only he can resolve it,'' writes biographer Slavoljub Djukic. ``He
is both the pyromaniac and the fireman.'' By RICK MONTGOMERY and
SCOTT CANON. Story will move in the ``w'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MS-KEVORKIAN-TWOTAKES (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) _ Regina Merrick never
knew Patricia Smith, but their paths seemed destined to cross. Like
Merrick, Smith was a nurse, a mother and an active member of the
Baptist Church. She also suffered from the same debilitating form
of multiple sclerosis. On Aug. 22, 1996, Smith, of Lee's Summit,
decided to end her pain with the aid of suicide doctor Jack
Kevorkian. Her death haunted Merrick, now 45, who read newspaper
articles and watched television reports about Smith's suicide in
Pontiac, Mich. Last week, as Kevorkian went on trial and was
convicted of second-degree murder, Merrick's thoughts turned to
Smith again. By MALCOLM GARCIA. Story will move in the ``a''
category..
</P>
