<HEADLINE>
SCHEDULE FOR `THE CENTURY'
</HEADLINE>
   (See also: CENTURY-TV-REVIEW, CENTURY-TV-MAKING) 
(rk) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here is the schedule of episodes in ``The Century.'' All are on
ABC from 9 to 11 p.m.:
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY: ``Heaven and Earth'' _ Part I: ``Lindbergh's Journey'';
Part II: ``First Step,'' on space exploration.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY: ``Ultimate Power'' _ Part I: ``Evil Rising,'' on
Hitler's rise to power; Part II: ``The Race,'' on the making of the
atomic bomb.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY: ``No Man's Land'' _ Part I: ``The Great War,'' on
World War I; Part II: ``The Fall,'' on the war in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
   APRIL 5: ``Memphis Dreams'' _ Part I: ``Innocence and
Rebellion,'' on Elvis Presley; Part II: ``Searching for the
Promised Land,'' on Martin Luther King Jr.
</P>
<P>
   APRIL 8: ``Coming Apart'' _ Part I: ``Nothing to Fear,'' on
Franklin D. Roosevelt; Part II: ``Picture This,'' on Hollywood
during the Cold War.
</P>
<P>
   APRIL 10: ``The Evolution of Revolution'' _ Part I: ``Live From
Tehran,'' on the hostage crisis brought home on television; Part
II: ``Facing the Millennium,'' putting the century in perspective.
</P>
<P>
   Peter Jennings is the anchor, and Tom Yellin is the executive
producer.
</P>
</TEXT>
