<HEADLINE>
HE'S AT EVERY RACE, AND ALWAYS MISSES FINISH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOHNNY D. BOGGS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
FORT WORTH, Texas _ Jody Muncus is a big racing fan. That's why he
arrived at Texas Motor Speedway at 1 p.m. Tuesday and why he was at
the track at 5 a.m. yesterday. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   That's why he will attend 36 NASCAR events this year. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   But the 27-year-old who hails from Booneville, N.C., won't see
one race from start to finish. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   That's because you'll find Muncus in the STP trailer, selling
merchandise for the Richard Petty-owned team that fields the No. 43
STP Pontiac driven by John Andretti. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll watch a little on TV,'' Muncus said. ``It'll die down a
little once the race starts, but I never get to see the beginning
or end of a race.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Such is life when you're part of the 13-member road crew selling
official souvenirs. Up at 3 a.m., leave the motel at 4, arrive at
the track at 5 and open the souvenir trailer at 6. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Then do it all again ... in Bristol, Tenn. ... Martinsville, Va.
... Talladega, Ala. ... Fontana, Calif. ... 17 states in 10 months,
and a lot of miles. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Muncus doesn't mind. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I drove trucks before I got this job, so it wasn't that big of
a change,'' said Muncus, in his first year hawking Andretti
merchandise. ``I like to travel anyway.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Business has been good at TMS, Muncus said, with sales ranking
up with the numbers at Daytona. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   So, who is Muncus' favorite driver? &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``John Andretti,'' he said quickly, even though it's 7 a.m. and
Muncus has been up for four hours. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   And who'll win the race? &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``John.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Just testing. &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
