<P>
   LA-STUDIES (Los Angeles) _ Without oversight or a way to gauge
effectiveness, Los Angeles city government spends nearly $20
million a year on average on an array of studies, from whether to
build a bigger airport to how to tax hot dog vendors. In addition,
records obtained by the Daily News show more than $73 million was
spent on outside consultant studies over the past four years. By
Beth Barrett. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MALL-GHOST-TOWN (Los Angeles) _ Once the sacred temple of
consumer culture and known nationwide as the ultimate teen hangout,
the Sherman Oaks Galleria is now a ghost town. The victim of
changing tastes and the Northridge earthquake, perhaps the most
famous shopping mall in history closes Thursday. By Steve Carney.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ Moviegoers continued to shower
affection on ``Forces of Nature'' as the romantic comedy took in an
estimated $9.6 million at 2,224 theaters to top a moderate national
box office, studio sources said Sunday. By Dave McNary. (Will move
in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
