   &UR; THE NET FILES  &LR; _ Conservative U.S. Senator Jon Kyl is rolling
the dice again in his personal crusade to rid the Internet of
gambling. By Jon Swartz
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BIOSCOPE  &LR;  _ Genetic forensics has become the newest and
perhaps most controversial tool in the crime fighter's
arsenal.That's especially true in cases like the Yosemite murders,
where bodies have been burned to destroy evidence, and bone
fragments or blood smears may be all that remains to establish
guilt. ``We only need a pinprick of material to make an
identification,'' said Sean Walsh, research director at the Applied
Biosystems division of Perkin-Elmer Corp. in Foster City. By Tom
Abate
</P>
