<HEADLINE>
MEMBER OF LOST BOYZ HIP HOP GROUP SLAIN
</HEADLINE>
   (jw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A member of the Lost Boyz, a popular hip hop group,
was shot to death early Sunday as he left a party at a Queens
hotel, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Raymond Rodgers, 28, who performed with the Lost Boyz under the
name Freaky Tah, was shot once in the head at 3:57 a.m. by a gunman
wearing a light blue ski mask as Rodgers was leaving the Four
Points Sheraton Hotel near Kennedy International Airport, said Sgt.
Gerry Falcon, police spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   Rodgers was taken to Jamaica Hospital Medical Center, where he
died a half hour later.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they did not know the motive, and detectives were
still looking for the gunman Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Lost Boyz, a group from Jamaica, Queens, was known for two
albums, ``Legal Drug Money'' and ``Love, Peace and Nappiness.'' The
Lost Boyz also had a hit song, ``Renee,'' which is about losing a
girlfriend to gunfire.
</P>
<P>
   Rodgers, who lived in Queens, is survived by two sons and a
daughter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
